<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
    <title>FAQ</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <let/q1=true>
    <let/q2=false>
    <let/q3=false>
    <const/openCount=[q1, q2, q3].filter(Boolean).length>
    <h1>FAQ</h1>
    <p>${openCount} open</p>
    <details>
      <summary>Is Marko fast?</summary>
      <p>Streaming SSR and a compiler that ships minimal JS. Yes.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do I need to import components?</summary>
      <p>Not if they live in a tags/ directory.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is HTML valid Marko?</summary>
      <p>Nearly all of it, yes.</p>
    </details>
    <button onClick() { q1 = q2 = q3 = false }>Collapse all</button>
  </body>
</html>
